Text.string: Still can't believe what Tyreen did to Lilith. When we catch up to that bitch, there's gonna be a reckoning.
The people of Athenas are gonna have to fend for themselves for a little while. More important things at stake.
So that Rhys guy's in charge of Atlas, huh? Like, the entire corporation, or is he just a figurehead? And was that mustache approved by the board of directors?
Maliwan just trashed my childhood home, and that Katagawa guy is a total douche. I am this close to throwing my SMG out the airlock.
Wrecking face on Athenas and taking the fight to Maliwan on an asteroid death laser. You're two for two in my book, Vault Hunter.
I thought the fragment would be safe on Athenas, but at least it's in good hands now. Powers or not, Lilith is still a badass, and that counts for something.
Been a while since I opened a Vault. But letting it fall into Tyreen Calypso's hands isn't an option. We have to get there first.
Keep an eye out for Lilith, yeah? I've known her a long time, and she's used to leading the charge. Gotta be tough leading from afar, you know?
The Calypsos are monsters. They're making Sirens look like dangerous psychopaths. Like it wasn't hard enough being in the crosshairs of every corporation in the Borderlands.
Well, Maliwan's still occupying Athenas, but at least the fragment's safe. That's gonna have to be good enough for now.
That's two fragments down. Wonder where the third one's hiding. Probably Rhys' mustache.
Sounds like you really saved Rhys' ass. Wish I could've joined you down there, but I had to keep up with Ava's training.
This ship is impressive. Not nearly as many oil stains and thumping noises as the old Sanctuary.
Hope the people of Athenas are all right.
Athenas will always be my home, but I almost miss Pandora.||—Almost.
We need a sign that says, “it's been this many nanoseconds since Claptrap's last screw up”. Just saying.
Keep on keepin' on, Vault Hunter.
